I came from Miami @ArtBasel back to London and then straight to Paris, not because I like pain, but mostly because there was no way I was missing the @Ledger event!

More on Miami later, but first a 'Postcard from Paris' on #LedgerOp3n. I made it to day two of the event... https://i.imgur.com/bayROKC.jpg

The excitement was palpable from the @ledger Stax announcement on the 6th + the demo by @tfadell.

There was a magnetic wall with Stax(es) that you could pull out, hold and take with you to get an idea of the product. It's light, easy to fit in a pocket/wallet. #LedgerOp3n https://i.imgur.com/cYqWGOW.jpg

I avoid scanning QR codes when out in the wild but it's different when its Ledger & their focus IS security.

The Infinity  NFT turned up in my wallet later. https://i.imgur.com/J4BpzvS.jpg

Snapshots from panel discussions.

"...identity is valuable, there's no reason to give it away to someone you don't trust. Web3 gives back power & data to the user & you can create incentives enforced by blockchain"
#LedgerOp3n https://i.imgur.com/d3Ntaxd.jpg

In the lead up to @nft_paris I attended a couple of lovely events.

First up: the @artblocks_io & @ledger takeover of @NFTFactoryParis, with a fab series of panels & events.

The talks were popular, it was standing room only by the time I arrived.

Here's what stuck with me... #NFTParis https://i.imgur.com/aUQZf7p.jpg

I attended the first panel specifically for Ismail of TRAME & @ArtOnBlockchain.

Context: @CPGCLUB, @ArtBlocksEngine & @trameparis have a unique collab; @MacTuitui's code will be fed into the digital loom of N√©olice, a French atelier to create a large scale physical tapestry.

I loved the way @IsmaTaziS described the collab as 'minting & weaving code'.

He says that the future of art & design will be expressed digitally & physically - retailers want to provide experiential & bespoke experiences - with beautiful pieces that trigger emotions. 

#NFTParis https://i.imgur.com/XIZvXjR.jpg

Ismail of TRAME went on to say that in the future, we'll see creative coders being hired by luxury brands - who would bring generative art to the masses.

Generative art is the perfect medium for brands. https://i.imgur.com/CRmt1nW.jpg

Speaking of brands, Snowfro said that it's all about staking your reputation on the right sort of brand.

Snowfro said he'd love to work with @Swatch & @LEGO_Group (somebody please make this happen!)
